race.comment: Originally a big field but decimated by scratchings  BIMBALLA (14) is fitter for two runs from a spell and finished fifth at each. Both were in far richer maidens and looks well placed here. Gets chance to break through. BRUISER MURPHY (3)  is a gelding by Exceedance on debut. Well educated but coming along well. winning the latest jump-out by a space. Looks primed for a forward showing. Watch the market very closely.  FULL OF KNOWLEDGE (4) stepped up to 1200m latest and raced in a far richer made  and was safely held. Back in trip and will find this easier. Was good the two starts prior over this trip and gets chance to bounce back.  TILLYA TEPE (13) is having first start. Well educated and expected to measure up.
